        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39148",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Why are you using getHelper()?\r\n\r\nThe intended use of the Dojo view helper is using Zend_View as a proxy: \r\n{code}\r\necho $this->dojo();\r\n{code}\r\nThis ensures that the appropriate method (Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Dojo::dojo()) is called, and that the return value from it is used. If you look at that method, it actually returns an instance of Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Dojo_Container, which contains toString() and __toString(), and which can be echoed both directly or by calling the toString() method.\r\n\r\n(The reason for this design is that the container object is placed in a registry, which ensures that it exists across multiple instances of Zend_View -- particularly useful when using partials.)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-10T10:46:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-10T10:46:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39155",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gerardroche",
                        "name": "gerardroche",
                        "displayName": "bullfrogblues",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Dojo_Container contains a \"__toString\" method but it does NOT contain a \"toString\" method, ZF 1.10.2.\r\n\r\n\r\necho $this->getHelper('dojo')->toString() is more instructive and concrete about what is actually happening than echo $this->dojo().\r\n\r\n+ though I'm sure it might be trivial it's one less \"call_user_func_array\" call & 1 less call to a method of the helper itself (i.e. the helper named method, e.g. in headMeta it's headMeta, (needless if you're not passing in any parameters). \r\n\r\nIf getHelper is not intended to be used this way it should be protected or not exist at all, I don't see any other use-case for it.\r\n\r\n\r\n\"This ensures that the appropriate method (Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Dojo::dojo()) is called, and that the return value from it is used ... (The reason for this design is that the container object is placed in a registry, which ensures that it exists across multiple instances of Zend_View - particularly useful when using partials.)\" \r\n\r\nView heleprs headMeta, headTitle, headLinks, etc are no different yet $this->getHelper('headMeta')->toString() works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gerardroche",
                        "name": "gerardroche",
                        "displayName": "bullfrogblues",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-11T01:45:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-11T01:45:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39156",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gerardroche",
                        "name": "gerardroche",
                        "displayName": "bullfrogblues",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "that was:\r\n\r\necho $this->getHelper('dojo')>toString() \r\n\r\nis more instructive and concrete about what is actually happening than \r\n\r\necho $this>dojo().\r\n\r\nThat wasn't supposed to be crossed out, but I'm not able to edit that comment. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gerardroche",
                        "name": "gerardroche",
                        "displayName": "bullfrogblues",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-11T01:48:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-11T01:48:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39161",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "getHelper() is primarily intended for retrieving the helper in order to inject dependencies; in most cases, you utilize helpers by calling them as methods of the view object.\r\n\r\nI'm re-opening this as a feature request.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-11T04:56:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-11T04:56:58.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
